such thing as driving quietly.</b></font>

134
00:10:40,384 --> 00:10:45,254
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Sometimes, he does these
"Hyaa!" or "Hngrar!" sorts of yells.</b></font>

135
00:10:45,254 --> 00:10:48,694
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Yeah, yeah! That sure is surprising, huh?</b></font>

136
00:10:48,694 --> 00:10:54,164
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I guess talking like that is
how Mr. Hoshino concentrates.</b></font>

137
00:10:54,164 --> 00:10:57,764
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Muttering to himself and
going into his own world...</b></font>

138
00:10:57,764 --> 00:11:02,774
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>We regular guys could never
duplicate something like that.</b></font>

139
00:11:02,774 --> 00:11:07,074
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Yeah. If you're trying to concentrate,
staying quiet is the normal way to do it.</b></font>

140
00:11:07,074 --> 00:11:09,274
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>That's exactly it.</i></b></font>

141
00:11:09,274 --> 00:11:14,384
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>When people are absorbed in something,</i>
<i>normally they don't engage in idle chatter.</i></b></font>

142
00:11:14,384 --> 00:11:18,254
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>But I know the real reason...</i></b></font>

143
00:11:22,124 --> 00:11:23,884
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Hngrar!</b></font>

144
00:11:25,364 --> 00:11:27,024
